The paper deals with mechanism design and auction theory, which are core topics in game theory (cs.GT) and theoretical computer science (cs.DS). The paper also involves optimization and approximation algorithms (cs.AI), as well as economic theory and market design (cs.EC). The use of duality and revenue non-monotonicity lemma suggests a connection to mathematical programming and optimization (cs.LG).
